Class Garage

  • java.lang.Object
    • Garage

  • public class Garage
extends java.lang.Object
    Garage is a public class that has all the methods needed to operate on Car objects. To use Garage, the external class/program will need code to create and hold a Garage object (to initiate the class), a NumberTile ArrayList (to hold the game board of tiles) and one NumberTile Arraylist per player

    • Method Detail

      • Arrive

        public java.lang.String Arrive(java.lang.String license)
        Arrive () is a mutator method that receives the license plate of a vehicle and checks to see if the garage is full. If there is room the method calls other processes to add the car in the last spot open
        Parameters:
        license - receives the license plate of a vehicle
        Returns:
        is a string with output stating the status of the operation

      • Depart

        public java.lang.String Depart(java.lang.String license)
        Depart() checks if the car is in the garage, if it is it calls other methods to remove the car. It then returns a status of the operation as a string
        Parameters:
        license - receives a license plate to look for
        Returns:
        a string with status of operation
